Uganda’s Peruth Chemutai was the surprise winner in the women’s 3000m steeplechase in the finals when she ripped apart an experienced field that included Kenyan duo of Beatrice Chepkoech and Hyvin Kiyeng. Chemutai crossed the finish line in 9:01.45 to win Uganda’s first gold medal at the Olympics as Courtney Frerichs of USA took silver in 9:04.79 while Kenya’s Hyvin Kiyeng settled for bronze in 9:05.39. World record holder Beatrice Chepkoech who had revealed that she was battling with a hamstring injury finished seventh in 9:16.33 Kenya is yet to win a gold medal in the women’s 3000m steeplechase since the event was introduced at the Olympics in 2008. More to follow… Also Read: Video Of The Day: KEMRI scientists examine safety of anti-malarial drugs in first trimester of pregnancy